commit.message:
Fix make clean rule (#50)

* Fix make clean rule

The make clean rule was missing a "then", so it wouldn't run properly.
This commit adds it, so now it works as it should.

* Send attachments in the order they were specified

Send attachments in the same order as they are specified in the command
line. They were previously sent in reverse order.

Fixes #13

* Send vcard as the last attachment

If any other attachments are attached, send the vcard as the last one.

* Remove mention to SIGNATURE_DIVIDE from manpage

SIGNATURE_DIVIDE is an obsolete option.

Debian packaging & allow using system dlib (#49)

* Allow using system dlib (useful for packaging in repositories)

* Allow setting custom version

* Debian packaging

* README.md: how to use system dlib

* add dlib-dev build dep
fix up finding -lssl

docdir suggestions

Don't install email.1 into docdir

Manual page is easier read using man and already installed to
mandir/man1.

Allow installer to define documentation directory

Traditionally docdir includes the full path to documentation directory
http://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/html_node/Directory-Variables.html

This allows distributions to append their package versioning to
directory name.

Maintain current default if --docdir is not passed to install.sh.

Bump minimum autoconf to 2.60

- Automake 2.0 will drop support for the long-deprecated 'configure.in'
